description: These blackberry cake pops have an extra POP, made with glitter in an ice cream mold.

recipe_json.name: Glitter Ice Cream Cake Pops
steps: Preheat a fan-forced oven to 160C (320F) or 180C (356F) for a conventional oven. Line a 20x15cm cake tin with baking paper. Set aside.

In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, add the flour, baking powder, caster sugar and salt. Turn mixer on low speed and allow it to mix for a couple minutes to help everything combine well (alternatively you may do this by sifting the ingredients together). Add the softened butter and let it mix until it resembles a fine sand like texture.
Next, add milk, eggs, yogurt, oil, blackberry flavouring and vanilla extract in a large jug and whisk well.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients in a slow and steady stream until no dry ingredients are visible. Scrape down the bowl and mix for another 20 seconds.
Pour batter into cake tin. Bake for 30 min or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Allow cake to cool completely.
Use your hands to crumble the cake in a large mixing bowl. Add frosting and mix until very well combined. Set aside.

Melt both green and pink chocolate in the microwave for 20 seconds at a time, mixing each time until smooth. Transfer each colour to a piping bag and pipe small squiggles into a silicone ice cream mold. You can grab these on amazon. It’s called a Silikomart Silicone Easy Ice Cream Bar Mold. It should come with the little ice cream sticks too.
Once you’ve piped the chocolate in there give the mold a wiggle to even it out.

Roll about 1 tsp of cake pop mixture between two hands, then into a log and flatten slightly. Add into the chocolate molds. Make sure the cake pop log isn’t sticking above the mold, you want it to be below the top of the mold because once you’ve gently pressed them in there you’re going to add some more chocolate on top. Give the mold a final wiggle to get rid of air bubbles.
Add ice cream sticks into the cake pops. Be gentle.
Gently take out of molds and brush with edible glitter.
ingredients: edible pink glitter (can be purchased from a cake decorating store or online)
